narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The natural continuation of Latin 110. This course concludes the instruction of Latin grammar and begins reading real Latin texts. I'd recommend this to anyone interested in the continued pursuit of Latin.

Latin 120 is the application of everything from Latin 110 with a lot of new vocabulary and a few new grammatical structures. It is a great overview of Latin texts, both prose and poetry. I would definitely recommend it to another student looking to improve their Latin skills.
A great class if you're interested in Latin.
Yes if you want to learn latin
